media: ipu6: prefer overlapping DPHY band with higher DDL osc target

get_hsfreq_by_mbps() searches freqranges[] backwards and returns the
higher band when adjacent bands overlap. At 1498 Mbps this selects the
1461-1640 band (osc_freq_target=208) instead of 1414-1588 (335); the
lower DDL target fails to lock and every frame arrives with payload
checksum (CRC) errors. Shift to the previous band when it also covers
the data rate and has a higher oscillation target.

Upstream: https://lore.kernel.org/linux-media/20260401162547.1597975-1-mnencia@kcore.it/T/
(accepted for 7.2; drop this patch once the running kernel contains it)

--- a/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu6/ipu6-isys-dwc-phy.c
+++ b/drivers/media/pci/intel/ipu6/ipu6-isys-dwc-phy.c
@@ -317,6 +317,19 @@
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * Adjacent frequency bands overlap. When the data rate also fits the
+	 * previous band and that band has a higher DDL target oscillation
+	 * frequency, prefer it: the lower target can fail to lock (e.g. at
+	 * 1498 Mbps), corrupting every frame with payload checksum errors.
+	 */
+	if (index > 0 &&
+	    mbps >= freqranges[index - 1].min &&
+	    mbps <= freqranges[index - 1].max &&
+	    freqranges[index - 1].osc_freq_target >
+	    freqranges[index].osc_freq_target)
+		index--;
+
 	dwc_dphy_write_mask(isys, phy_id, IPU6_DWC_DPHY_HSFREQRANGE,
 			    freqranges[index].hsfreq, 0, 7);
 
